g.text: FAN_CONTROL must be connected to a PWM pin that is
connected to any of Timer/Counter1, 3, or 4 (meaning pins
D5, D6, D9, D10, D11, or D13 are acceptable).
The tachometer signal is an open-collector, two pulse
per revolution square wave that needs to be pulled up
to 12V. The Noctua datasheet also specifies a maximum
current of no more than 5mA. In addition, the Arduino
has a maximum of 5V for its inputs. To satisfy these
constraints, there's a pull up to 12V (R4), followed by a
voltage divider to bring the 12V down to 5V.
Other resistor values can be used as long as they satisfy
those constraints. I picked these values as I already had
The fan control signal is a 5V,
TEMP_INPUT must be connected to an analog input pin.
TACH_INPUT must be connected to an external interrupt pin.
